<subSubSection id="B75085B5939BB12BE0C3873C7576E974" pageId="0" pageNumber="193" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="9AD9BFD11B3F71ABE9DA8CC005A53B6D" pageId="0" pageNumber="193">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="58B257B6A6366122B7EE5F28D935A4DA" pageId="0" pageNumber="193">
Verity (1923) proposed this name as a race of 
<taxonomicName id="98D217B14D8EED82DBB57B6E23C2038F" class="Insecta" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. ergane" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="193" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ergane">
<emphasis id="C3AF48658CBA0C54DDEFA89F67E041BA" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="193">P. ergane</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Geyer, 1828). According to 
<bibRefCitation id="A93057BD1D895EBED30CCD7D14A06C4A" author="Kudrna, O" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Research on the Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="193" pagination="1 - 105" refId="B56" refString="Kudrna, O, 1983. An annotated catalogue of the butterflies named by Roger Verity. Journal of Research on the Lepidoptera 21 (1): 1 - 105" title="An annotated catalogue of the butterflies named by Roger Verity." volume="21" year="1983">Kudrna (1983)</bibRefCitation>
, this name in unavailable because it is a seasonal form and also a nomen nudum. The year on the specimen labels (1937) indicate specimens were collected 14 years after description (1923) from the same location the original holotype material was collected. As a result, the black label of the specimens treated as 
<normalizedToken id="51B71B9E9383915AB5A36CFD2EF55230" originalValue="“types”">&quot;types&quot;</normalizedToken>
is erroneous. The specimen collected from the same geographical location from which the type specimen was collected is called topotype. According to ICZN (1999), a topotype has no formal standing and is not regulated by the Code. Therefore, these two specimens are erroneously labelled as types, should be annotated as &quot;Not a Type&quot; and are treated here as 
<normalizedToken id="90DCD0CFC8578206FB91B0333810F5AC" originalValue="“Non-type”">&quot;Non-type&quot;</normalizedToken>
specimens.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
